$ /boot/grub/grub.cfg

The configuration file for → Linux/booting/GRUB/index (usually located under → Linux/fhs/boot/grub/index).

Created by Linux/shell/commands/grub-mkconfig.

This file controls the operation of → Linux/shell/commands/grub-mkconfig.

It should be a valid → Linux/POSIX shell script because it is sourced.

Usually, it contains just `KEY=value` lines.

Valid keys are
  • GRUB_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_SAVEDEFAULT
  • GRUB_TIMEOUT
  • GRUB_HIDDEN_TIMEOUT
  • GRUB_HIDDEN_TIMEOUT_QUIET
  • GRUB_DEFAULT_BUTTON
  • GRUB_TIMEOUT_BUTTON
  • GRUB_HIDDEN_TIMOOUT_BUTTON
  • GRUB_BUTTON_CMOS_ADDRESS
  • GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR
  • GRUB_TERMINAL_INPUT
  • GRUB_TERMINAL_OUTPUT
  • GRUB_TERMINAL
  • GRUB_SERIAL_COMMAND
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_NETBSD
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_NETBSD_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_GNUMACH
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_XEN
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_XEN_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_XEN_REPLACE
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_XEN_REPLACE_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX_DEFAULT
  • GRUB_DISABLE_LINUX_UUID
  • GRUB_DISABLE_RECOVERY
  • GRUB_VIDEO_BACKEND
  • GRUB_GFXMODE
  • GRUB_BACKGROUND
  • GRUB_THEME
  • GRUB_GFXPAYLOAD_LINUX
  • GRUB_DISABLE_OS_PROBER
  • GRUB_INIT_TUNE
  • GRUB_BADRAM
  • GRUB_PRELOAD_MODULES
